# AC4 / AC8: `head` applied to a Tuple yields the precise first-element type.
# `head([42, "hello"])` synthesises `number` (not `number | string` or `any`).
# Without AC8, the result would be `any`.
#
# `tail([42, "hello"])` synthesises `Tuple([string])`.
# `head(tail([42, "hello"]))` therefore synthesises `string`.

` { type: "number" }
hd: [42, "hello"] head

` { type: "string" }
tl-hd: [42, "hello"] tail head
